sed on something from the 1950s or 1960s and watch what happens.
Second is the recent resurgence in nuclear power driven by the tech giants=
=E2=80=99 demand for huge amounts of clean, reliable energy to power their =
AI data centers.=C2=A0
Nuclear power is an old idea, from the 1930s and 1940s, and one that Americ=
a implemented rapidly through the 1960s and 1970s, when it seemed as if the=
 demand for electricity would continue to grow apace with the Henry Adams C=
urve. It didn=E2=80=99t.=C2=A0
There are a lot of reasons that nuclear power fell off. The NRC is certainl=
y partially to blame =E2=80=93 at the very least, they=E2=80=99ve made it m=
uch more difficult and expensive to build and iterate on nuclear technology=
=2E But one important reason that nucle=
ar fell off is that the demand just wa=
sn=E2=80=99t there.=C2=A0
Now, the demand is back. Microsoft is restarting Three Mile Island. Amazon =
is investing in Small Modular Reactors. Google is buying up to 500 MW of po=
